  "text": "Electric cleaning achieves the effect of removing contaminants by applying an applied electric field on the film at a certain time interval to cause the contaminating particles to move away from the film surface in the direction of the electric field. However, this method requires that the film has a conductive function, or that the electrode can be mounted on the film surface, so that it is used less [CITATION_1] .",
